      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I'm not a fan of the `std::optional<bool>` cache approach, it's an error-prone API imo (even if it's private and small). I think it makes more sense to just calculate the boolean at initialization and follow the same pattern as for `hash` and `m_witness_hash`? It has to be calculated for every instance anyway.\r\n\r\nAs e.g. in https://github.com/stickies-v/bitcoin/commit/2e69a6597c1a07b319e9cba4601474fbe0761f71",
